spans.text: my cause of woe ! — Kirmor , thou hast lost no son
the dark heath ! streams of the mountains , roar !
my mind that sad night , when all my children fell ; when Arindel the mighty fell ; when Daura the lovely died
fair as the moon on the hills of Jura
fair was the hope of their friends
disguised like a son of the sea : fair was his skiff on the wave ; white his locks of age
it is Daura who calls thee ! — Earch the traitor fled laughing to the land
it is Daura who calls thee ! — Earch the traitor fled laughing to the land
for her brother and her father
in the spoils of the chase
the surgy deep in his boat , to bring Daura to the land
OH Arindel my son ! for Earch the traitor thou diedest
among the grass of the rocks
when the north lifts the waves on high
see the ghosts of my children
